.Dd April 17, 2026
.Dt MANEATER.TOML 5
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm maneater.toml
.Nd configuration file for maneater
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is the configuration file for
.Xr maneater 1 .
It uses TOML format and controls model selection, embedding prefixes,
manpath discovery, and corpus definitions.
.Sh FILE HIERARCHY
Configuration files are loaded and merged in order:
.Bl -enum
.It
.Ev MANEATER_CONFIG
(base; lowest priority).
When set, this file is loaded first.
The Nix wrapper sets this to a bundled configuration with pre-resolved
model paths and a default manpages corpus.
.It
.Pa $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/maneater/maneater.toml
(global; defaults to
.Pa ~/.config/maneater/maneater.toml
when
.Ev XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is unset).
Falls back to
.Pa $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/maneater/models.toml
if the primary file does not exist.
.It
Each parent directory between
.Ev HOME
and the current working directory.
.It
.Pa ./maneater.toml
(project-local).
.El
.Pp
Later files override earlier ones.
Models are merged by name; keys from the overlay replace keys in the base,
while unset keys are preserved.
Manpath include lists accumulate: they are appended across hierarchy levels.
The
.Va manpath.no-auto
field is replaced entirely if present in an overlay.
The
.Va storage
table is replaced entirely if present in an overlay
.Pq not merged field-by-field .
.Sh TOP-LEVEL KEYS
.Bl -tag -width "default"
.It Va default
Name of the default model.
Must match a key in the
.Va models
table.
Required when multiple models are configured; optional when only one
model exists (that model is used automatically).
.El
.Sh MODELS
Each model is a sub-table under
.Va models
keyed by an arbitrary name.
.Bl -tag -width "document-prefix"
.It Va path
Absolute path to a GGUF model file.
Supports
.Ev $VAR
and
.Ev ${VAR}
environment variable expansion.
Required.
.It Va query-prefix
String prepended to queries before embedding.
Used for asymmetric search models.
Optional.
.It Va document-prefix
String prepended to documents before embedding.
Optional.
.El
.Pp
Example with multiple models:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
default = "snowflake"

[models.snowflake]
path = "/opt/models/snowflake-arctic-embed-l-v2.0-q8_0.gguf"
query-prefix = "query: "

[models.nomic]
path = "/opt/models/nomic-embed-text-v1.5.Q8_0.gguf"
query-prefix = "search_query: "
document-prefix = "search_document: "
.Ed
.Sh MANPATH
The
.Va manpath
table controls how
.Nm maneater
discovers man pages beyond the system
.Xr manpath 1 .
.Pp
By default,
.Nm maneater
probes the current working directory for common in-repo man page locations:
.Pp
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
.Pa man/
.It
.Pa doc/man/
.It
.Pa share/man/
.El
.Pp
Directories that exist are prepended to the system manpath, so project pages
shadow system pages with the same name.
.Bl -tag -width "include"
.It Va include
Array of additional directories to prepend to the manpath.
Relative paths are resolved from the current working directory.
Supports
.Ev $VAR
and
.Ev ${VAR}
environment variable expansion.
Include lists accumulate across hierarchy levels.
.It Va no-auto
When set to
.Cm true ,
disables heuristic probing of
.Pa man/ ,
.Pa doc/man/ ,
and
.Pa share/man/ .
Only explicit
.Va include
paths and the system manpath are used.
Default:
.Cm false .
.El
.Pp
Example:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[manpath]
include = ["vendor/man", "${PROJECT_ROOT}/result/share/man"]
.Ed
.Pp
To disable heuristic probing in a project:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[manpath]
no-auto = true
.Ed
.Sh CORPORA
Corpora define the document sources to index and search.
Each corpus is an array-of-tables entry under
.Va [[corpora]] .
.Pp
When no
.Va [[corpora]]
sections are present, an implicit manpages corpus is used.
When any
.Va [[corpora]]
sections are defined, only those corpora are indexed.
To include man pages alongside other corpora, add an explicit manpages entry.
.Pp
All corpus types share these fields:
.Bl -tag -width "max-chars"
.It Va name
Unique identifier for the corpus.
Used as the cache directory name.
Required for
.Va files
and
.Va command
types.
.It Va type
Corpus type.
One of
.Cm manpages ,
.Cm files ,
or
.Cm command .
Required.
.It Va max-chars
Maximum characters per document text.
Longer texts are truncated before embedding.
Default: 500.
Optional.
.El
.Ss manpages
Scans the system manpath (and any configured include paths) for man pages.
Extracts synopses via
.Xr mandoc 1
and
.Xr pandoc 1 ,
and enriches with
.Xr tldr 1
descriptions.
No additional fields required.
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[corpora]]
type = "manpages"
.Ed
.Ss files
Indexes text files matching glob patterns.
Binary files (detected by null bytes) are skipped.
.Bl -tag -width "paths"
.It Va paths
Array of glob patterns to match files.
Required.
.El
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[corpora]]
name = "project-docs"
type = "files"
paths = ["docs/**/*.md", "README.md"]
max-chars = 1000
.Ed
.Ss command
Indexes documents produced by external commands.
.Bl -tag -width "read-cmd"
.It Va list-cmd
Command array that outputs one document key per line to stdout.
Required.
.It Va read-cmd
Command array that receives a key as its final argument and outputs
document text to stdout.
Required.
.El
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[corpora]]
name = "wiki"
type = "command"
list-cmd = ["wiki-tool", "list"]
read-cmd = ["wiki-tool", "read"]
.Ed
.Sh STORAGE
The
.Va storage
table configures the content-addressed blob store used to persist index
blobs.
The store is the sole storage for index entries; it must be initialized
before indexing or searching.
See
.Xr maneater 1
.Sx BLOB STORAGE
for an overview.
.Pp
When no
.Va [storage]
section is present (or only
.Va store-id
is set), maneater uses
.Xr madder 1
as the default backend:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[storage]
store-id = "maneater"
.Ed
.Bl -tag -width "exists-cmd"
.It Va store-id
Identifier passed to the backend.
For the
.Xr madder 1
default, also used as the store name by
.Cm init-store
and
.Cm index .
Default:
.Dq maneater .
.It Va read-cmd
Optional.
Command array whose invocation receives the blob digest as the final
positional argument.
Stdout is the raw blob.
Non-zero exit is treated as "blob not found or error".
Setting this (or
.Va write-cmd )
switches maneater off the builtin madder backend.
.It Va write-cmd
Optional.
Command array that reads a blob from stdin and writes a digest
identifying it to stdout.
The digest is parsed from the last TAP
.Dq ok N \- <digest>
line, or, failing that, the first whitespace-delimited token on the
last non-empty line.
.It Va exists-cmd
Optional.
Command array whose exit status reports whether the configured store
exists.
Non-zero exit is treated as
.Dq not exists
(maneater
.Cm index
fails fast with a pointer to
.Cm init-store ).
When
.Va exists-cmd
is unset, the store is assumed to exist and the fast-fail check is
skipped.
Lines in stdout may have the form
.Dq <name>: <type>
(same shape as
.Xr madder 1 Ql list ),
in which case maneater looks for a line whose name token matches
.Va store-id .
.It Va init-cmd
Optional.
Command array run by
.Cm init-store
to create the backing store.
Unset means initialization is a no-op.
.El
.Pp
A non-default madder store (same builtin backend, different store ID):
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[storage]
store-id = "my-index-store"
.Ed
.Pp
A generic command-based backend \(em here, a filesystem tree keyed by
SHA-256:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[storage]
store-id = "local-sha256"
read-cmd  = ["sh", "-c", "cat \(dq$BLOBS/$1\(dq", "--"]
write-cmd = ["sh", "-c", "d=$(mktemp -p \(dq$BLOBS\(dq .in.XXXXXX); cat >\(dq$d\(dq; h=$(sha256sum \(dq$d\(dq|awk '{print $1}'); mv \(dq$d\(dq \(dq$BLOBS/$h\(dq; echo $h", "--"]
exists-cmd = ["sh", "-c", "test -d \(dq$BLOBS\(dq && echo \(dq$1: local fs\(dq", "--", "local-sha256"]
init-cmd   = ["sh", "-c", "mkdir -p \(dq$BLOBS\(dq"]
.Ed
.Pp
(Requires
.Ev BLOBS
to be set in the environment before invocation; any command array works
\(em madder, curl wrappers, aws-cli shims, etc.)
.Sh EXAMPLES
Minimal configuration with a single model (no
.Va default
needed):
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[models.snowflake]
path = "/opt/models/snowflake-arctic-embed-l-v2.0-q8_0.gguf"
query-prefix = "query: "
.Ed
.Pp
Index Go source files in a project alongside man pages:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[corpora]]
type = "manpages"

[[corpora]]
name = "project-src"
type = "files"
paths = ["cmd/**/*.go", "internal/**/*.go"]
max-chars = 1000
.Ed
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width "MANEATER_CONFIG"
.It Ev MANEATER_CONFIG
Path to a base configuration file loaded as the lowest-priority layer
in the hierarchy described above.
User and project configs overlay on top of it.
The Nix wrapper sets this to a bundled configuration with pre-resolved
model paths and a default manpages corpus.
.It Ev XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for the global configuration file.
Defaults to
.Pa ~/.config .
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr madder 1 ,
.Xr maneater 1 ,
.Xr toml 5
